			<div class="post">
	
				<h2><a href="http://www.shiningtrends.com/best-fall-buys/do-you-dare-to-wear-the-midi/" title="Do you dare to wear the MIDI?">Do you dare to wear the MIDI?</a></h2>
	
				<div class="postinfo">
	Lizzie - <a href="http://www.shiningtrends.com/category/best-fall-buys/" title="View all posts in Best Fall Buys" rel="category tag">Best Fall Buys</a>  
				</div>
	
				<div class="entry">
	
						<p style="text-align: center;">Midi lengths seem to be everywhere this season and with them a new balance in the silhouettes. The waist gets highlighted better - you can use belts or peplums in order to do so, but also the shape becomes tighter and more body-centric.  Not to mention how much sexier this lenght is, especially when wearing heels. :)</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Balmain,  Nina Ricci or Christian Dior have all played with the length, will you?</strong></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">
<p style="text-align: center;"><img src="http://i244.photobucket.com/albums/gg11/shiningtrends/balmain-midi-dress-trend-fall-2012-2013.jpg" border="0" alt="Midi Dress - Balmain Fall Winter 2012 - 2013, Midi Dress - Balmain Fall Winter 2012 - 2013" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Balmain - Fall Winter 2012 - 2013</p>
